<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-29T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="779" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2939: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-29T15:00:00-05:00">December 29, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:08 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>177. Authorities closed Habana Yacht Club yesterday afternoon, alleging
                            that building was being used as meeting place by persons conspiring
                            against the Government. This measure affects only the best social
                            element among whom it has engendered increased bitterness toward
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>